Constructor Detail

ElementMechLoad

public ElementMechLoad(java.lang.String name,
                       BoundaryCase bCase,
                       int type,
                       int component,
                       DVec values)
Creates element mechanical load.

Parameters:
name - The name of element mechanical load.
bCase - The boundary case of element mechanical load.
type - The type of mechanical load.
component - The component of mechanical load.
values - The values vector of mechanical load. For line load, it has two components denoting the loading values at I-th and J-th ends. For area load, it has three components denoting the loading values at three successive corners starting from lower left corner and in counter-clockwise order. For volume load, it has one component denoting the uniform distribution of load over the element.
